The Chairperson of the African Youth Leaders Roundtable, Comrade Ben Duntoye has called on Kogi youths across the country to support Kogi State Governor, Alhaji Yahaya Bello and Chief Edward Onoja for a second term. Ben Duntoye, who was a former Commissioner for Information in Kwara State made this known on Monday while speaking with newsmen. The former President of the Pan African Youth Union and also former National Youth Council President noted that it is very important for the people to rally round the governor so that he can complete the numerous people-oriented projects presently going on in the state. He said that nomination of the Chief of Staff to the governor, Chief Edward Onoja as running mate to Governor Yahaya Bello is a good omen and has shown that he has what it takes to be deputy governor of Kogi State. Nigeria @ 59: Nigeria will be sitting on time bomb if…… #NigeriaAt59: President Buhari’s Independence Day speech… Kidnappers yet to release wife of railway boss as police… Nigeria@59: 9-year-old Ifeanyichukwu, nine others grab… ALSO READ: NSE revenue dropped to N7.67bn in 2018 over uncertainties ― Onyema He stressed that Onoja has contributed so much to national development and Kogi in particular as a good ambassador of Nigerian youth as he represents the younger generation “Since the governor has been tested, trusted and has just another four years to spend in office, it is wiser for the people of the state to vote for him instead of another experiment with another Governorship candidate. “One good term deserves another. Bello/Onoja candidacy is a welcome development. It is good for the state, women, young people, workers should vote for them because I believe he will perform very very well. “Another 4 years of Yahaya Bello will bring about consolidation of landmark achievements and greater youth empowerment and youth involvement in decision making progress,” he said. How premature ejaculation  and small penis almost ruin my marriage and made my wife